00%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:0;transition-delay:500ms\"/><picture><source srcSet=\"/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/43fa5/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 250w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/c6e3d/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 500w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/af104/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 999w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/5ece7/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 999px) 100vw, 999px\"/><img sizes=\"(max-width: 999px) 100vw, 999px\" srcSet=\"/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/43fa5/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 250w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/c6e3d/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 500w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/af104/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 999w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/5ece7/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/af104/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png\" alt=\"The PM Group - Gala Check Presentation\" loading=\"eager\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"/></picture><noscript><picture><source srcset=\"/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/43fa5/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 250w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/c6e3d/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 500w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/af104/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 999w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/5ece7/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 999px) 100vw, 999px\" /><img loading=\"eager\" sizes=\"(max-width: 999px) 100vw, 999px\" srcset=\"/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/43fa5/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 250w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/c6e3d/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 500w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/af104/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 999w,\n/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/5ece7/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png 1200w\" src=\"/static/ea6c45e28e0f034f2d2ce8eb93eafaef/af104/Image-11.22.19-2019-Gala-Check-Presentation.png\" alt=\"The PM Group - Gala Check Presentation\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">In September, The PM Group hosted the 2019 Kings and Queens of Good Hearts Fun-Raiser benefiting local San Antonio charities. Although our day to day work consists of strategic marketing, creative development, and media buying, some of our favorite work is when we pull together to host events that support the community we are proud to call home.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">“We are so honored to bring together eleven diverse non-profit groups and help them raise funds which make such a positive impact on our community. Additionally, we are so grateful to all the generous sponsors, donors, volunteers, and guests who give their time, energy and support which made our 2019 Kings  &amp; Queens of Good Hearts gala a huge success,” said The PM Group founder and CEO, Bob Wills.</p>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">Thanks to everyone in attendance, this year’s gala was able to raise $474,753! Without the generous support from staff, volunteers, sponsors, and attendees, this wouldn’t have been possible. We are excited to share the following amounts raised for our charities this year:</p>\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">\n<u>ANIMAL RESCUE &amp; WELFARE:</u><br />\nCressie Animal Refuge &amp; Enrichment<br />\nGod’s Dogs Rescue<br />\nMission: Miracle K9 Rescue<br />\nSan Antonio Zoo<br />\n<strong>A total of $76,023.55</strong>\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">\n<u>HEALTH &amp; FAMILY SERVICES</u><br />\nGuide Dogs of Texas<br />\nSan Antonio Sports<br />\n<strong>A total of $89,496.95</strong>\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">\n<u>EDUCATION</u><br />\nCentral Catholic High School<br />\nSA YES<br />\n<strong>A total of $209,671.14</strong>\n</div>\n<div style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">\n<u>CHILD HEALTH &amp; WELFARE</u><br />\nChildren’s Bereavement Center of South Texas<br />\nThe Children’s Shelter<br />\n<strong>A total of $50,322.36</strong>\n</div>\n<div  style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\">\n<u>RETIRED &amp; ACTIVE MILITARY</u><br />\nSoldiers’ Angels<br />\n<strong>A total of $49,239.59</strong>\n</div>\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: .75rem;\"><a href=\"https://thepmgrp.com\"><strong>About The PM Group</strong></a>: The PM Group was founded in 1988. For over 30 years, the agency has continued to grow and is San Antonio’s largest advertising agency. The PM Group’s client roster spans numerous industries including automotive, CPG, entertainment and sports marketing, legal, business services, non-profit, real estate and fitness. In addition, the agency hosts an annual Charity Gala that to date has raised millions of dollars for local San Antonio area non-profit organizations in the last 15 years! In the past 5 years, The PM Group has raised both directly and indirectly over $3.5 million for these charities. It is our way of giving back to the community that we so humbly serve.</p>\n","title":"Over $470,000 Raised for San Antonio Charities","seo":{"breadcrumbs":[{"text":"Over $470,000 Raised for San Antonio Charities","url":"/470000-raised-for-san-antonio-charities/"}],"title":"Over $470,000 Raised for San Antonio Charities | The PM Group","metaDesc":"In September, The PM Group hosted the 2019 Kings and Queens of Good Hearts Fun-Raiser benefiting local San Antonio charities and raised over $470,000...","focuskw":"Kings and Queens of Good Hearts Fun-Rais